s their inner values.\n\n   ```ocaml\n   let variable = 42 in\n   let { x; _ } = point in\n   let Some x = optional in\n   (* ... *)\n   ```\n\nBeware that pattern matching on only one of many possible values will lead to runtime errors!\n"},"span":{"start":44,"end":44}},{"kind":{"id":"E0008","name":"invalid-expression","expected":"expression","found":{"kind":"{","text":"{"},"hint":"Expected a value, function call, or operator expression."},"span":{"start":44,"end":44}},{"kind":{"id":"E0005","name":"unexpected-structure-item","expected":"structure item (e.g., let, type, module)","found":{"kind":"->","text":"->"},"hint":"Structure items are top-level declarations like let, type, or module."},"span":{"start":73,"end":74}},{"kind":{"id":"E0005","name":"unexpected-structure-item","expected":"structure item (e.g., let, type, module)","found":{"kind":"identifier","text":"y"},"hint":"Structure items are top-level declarations like let, type, or module."},"span":{"start":75,"end":76}}]}
